\lim_{t\to\infty}
\bigg\|\,
2\varepsilon\Bigl(\frac{\Delta\rho_t^\varepsilon}{\rho_t^\varepsilon}
   -\frac{\Delta\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}{\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}\Bigr)
\bigg\|
\]

\[
= \lim_{t\to\infty}
\Bigg\|\,
2\varepsilon\,\frac{\rho_\infty^\varepsilon\,\Delta\rho_t^\varepsilon
   -\rho_t^\varepsilon\,\Delta\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}
{\rho_t^\varepsilon\,\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}
\Bigg\|
\]

\[
= \lim_{t\to\infty}
\Bigg\|\,
2\varepsilon\,\frac{
   \rho_\infty^\varepsilon\bigl(\Delta\rho_t^\varepsilon-\Delta\rho_\infty^\varepsilon\bigr)
   +\Delta\rho_\infty^\varepsilon\bigl(\rho_\infty^\varepsilon-\rho_t^\varepsilon\bigr)
}{\rho_t^\varepsilon\,\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}
\Bigg\|
\]

\[
= \lim_{t\to\infty}
\bigg\|\,
2\varepsilon\,\frac{\Delta\bigl(\rho_t^\varepsilon-\rho_\infty^\varepsilon\bigr)}
   {\rho_t^\varepsilon}
\;+\;
2\varepsilon\,\frac{\Delta\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}{\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}
   \,\frac{\rho_\infty^\varepsilon-\rho_t^\varepsilon}{\rho_t^\varepsilon}
\bigg\|
\]

\[
2\varepsilon\Biggl[
      \frac{\displaystyle\Delta\!\bigl(\rho_t^\varepsilon-\rho_\infty^\varepsilon\bigr)}
           {\rho_t^\varepsilon\,\mu_t}
      \;+\;
      \frac{\displaystyle\Delta\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}{\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}\,
      \frac{\rho_\infty^\varepsilon-\mu_t\,\rho_t^\varepsilon}
           {\rho_t^\varepsilon\,\mu_t}
\Biggr]
\]

Here is the corrected algebra with \(\mu_t\) **dividing** the original denominator \( \rho_t^\varepsilon \):

\[
2\varepsilon\!
\left(\frac{\Delta\rho_t^\varepsilon}{\rho_t^\varepsilon/\mu_t}
      -\frac{\Delta\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}{\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}\right)
\;=\;
2\varepsilon\!\left(
      \mu_t\,\frac{\Delta\rho_t^\varepsilon}{\rho_t^\varepsilon}
      -\frac{\Delta\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}{\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}
\right).
\]

Putting the two terms over the common denominator \( \rho_t^\varepsilon\rho_\infty^\varepsilon \) and then splitting the numerator exactly as before gives

\[
2\varepsilon\Biggl[
      \mu_t\,\frac{\Delta\!\bigl(\rho_t^\varepsilon-\rho_\infty^\varepsilon\bigr)}
                 {\rho_t^\varepsilon}
      \;+\;
      \frac{\Delta\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}{\rho_\infty^\varepsilon}\;
      \frac{\mu_t\,\rho_\infty^\varepsilon-\rho_t^\varepsilon}
           {\rho_t^\varepsilon}
\Biggr].
\]

Everything now involves denominators of the form \( \rho_t^\varepsilon \) (with the desired \(\mu_t\) factor sitting in the numerators), so the division-by-\(\mu_t\) correction is applied consistently.

